name local.misc.insult
author Alexander Boyd
description Adds a factoid, ~insult, that says a random insult of the form "Hey <person>, 
  you <adjective> <noun> of <adjective> <noun>". For example, "~insult someperson" might 
  respond with "Hey someperson, you decrepit piece of moldy filth". Right now, this factpack 
  refuses to insult jcp, the creator of the bot.
>insult {firstvar|person|%1%|%0%}{lset|person|{ifeq|%person%|jcp|%0%|%person%}}
 Hey %person%, you {exact|insult1} {exact|insult2} of {exact|insult3} {exact|insult4}
>insult1 {random|stupid|idiotic|infuriating|distended|rat-faced|driveling|decrepit|incompetent|dumb|pathetic|lame|son-of-a-gun}
>insult2 {random|piece|chunk|bag|pile|mountain|vat|blob|bin|trash can|dumpster}
>insult3 {random|moldy|grimey|cute|sloshy|foul|spoiled|contaminated|cheesy|soppy|wormy}
>insult4 {random|armpit hairs|filth|mold|parrot droppings|rat bogies|shark snot|pustulence|sinus clots|whale waste|acne}
